  "year_intro": "<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong><em>\"I discovered New York from The Pierre\".</em> </strong><br /><strong>- Karl Lagerfeld </strong></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">During the 1970's,The Pierre becomes the center of the fashion world in New York. <strong>Valentino</strong> hosts couture shows at the hotel. <strong>Karl Lagerfeld, Cher</strong> and <strong>Barbra Streisand</strong> are all regulars. In addition to hosting galas, social events and the most opulent weddings, The Pierre's legendary ballrooms and entertainment spaces remain the premier venue for such notable fashion industry events as the <strong>Women's Wear Daily Awards and L'Oreal's Women of Worth Honors. </strong></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">In 1973, Hotel Pierre is officially renamed The Pierre when it becomes a <strong>Trusthouse Forte</strong> property. Legendary British hotelier, <strong>Sir Rocco Forte</strong> introduces afternoon tea at the hotel, a beloved tradition that continues today.</p>"
